<cl=A2A2A2>
Like any other magicians guild, Inquisitors somewhat dislike warriors, so there is no access here to those advanced in soldiering. Inquisitors have entirely devoted themselves to the teaching of the Weaver, so they only know the magic he used, the magic of fire, and they know it perfectly. It is thanks to this magic that inquisitors have powerful protection from both military and magical attacks. As for their attacks, empowered by the magic of fire they make one treat Inquisitors with due respect. The magic of purification that is only conceivable to them can strip the enemy of a lot of magical advantages, the magic of fetters can cuff the enemy's hands, and Revival can help get rid of a tiresome enemy by sending him to monsters.
<br><br>
